Package: csDAM
Title: csDAM: Cosine Similarity-based Discriminative Analysis of Mixtures
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Dongping", "Du", , "dpdu@vt.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: csDAM, a cosine similarity–based discriminative analysis of mixtures method, specifically designed to deconvolute highly-mixed bulk expression data. Facilitated by the monotonic relationship between signature gene specificity and cosine similarity rank distribution, csDAM achieves highly accurate estimation of cell type proportions and specific expressions. Simulation and real-data based studies show both improved deconvolution performance and computational efficiency by csDAM compared to most-relevant peer methods.
